oder", "start": "4351.470","u": "Yes . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4352.044","u": "And . . . ah . . . it&#39;s occupied now and I couldn&#39;t get it back."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4356.049","u": "How . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4356.232","u": "I have been back for more than a year and I . . . I can&#39;t get in."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4359.750","u": "Tell me, why . . . who lives there?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4362.141","u": "There is a man who was once a prisoner in Germany."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4366.613","u": "Yes . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4366.816","u": "He came back in &#39;42 and fought the Free [?] and he has a military requisition."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4371.608","u": "Ah . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4372.258","u": "And . . . ah . . . even though this requisition have . . . ah . . . no more sense now the war being over . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4378.446","u": "No more value."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4379.608","u": "Yes. I can&#39;t get him out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4381.619","u": "And . . . eh . . . that is why you can&#39;t bring your children over?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4384.467","u": "That&#39;s why I can&#39;t bring my children back with me to Paris; and they need it very badly because they&#39;re in a . . . quite a small place where there is no good school. My daughter is nine years [?]. She ought to speak a second language by now . . . by now; and . . . ah . . . no kind of education and nothing at all. I&#39;m very worried about her."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4401.533","u": "Eh . . . tell me . . . ah . . . you are here with the . . . with the Joint Distribution Committee?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4407.792","u": "Yes, I work with . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4408.193","u": "How did you find them; to work for them?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4412.163","u": "I knew a lady who was working for the Joint and I had met her once in . . . in these critical days in &#39;42 when we . . . everybody was trembling to be arrested. She just came to see me. She was a friend of my governess."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4426.244","u": "Hm . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4427.001","u": "And she was working here, and when I came back to my governess I got in touch with her, and she . . . eh . . . she got me here."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4432.985","u": "Your governess was never deported?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4434.772","u": "No, she slipped through."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4436.691","u": "She lived through."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4437.437","u": "But was very . . . she was awfully kind as well as [?] . . . it was very lucky for me because she took care of the children, really as if they had been hers."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4445.129","u": "Yes. Tell me, Mrs. Bondy, you were . . . since you were near the . . . ah . . . Nazi now and then in the office, what were they talking? Did they believe they will win the war and all that?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4457.013","u": "I don&#39;t think they did. Finally they did not. They were supposed to make us believe that they would win the war, and I remember after the . . . the Americans had come to Paris that . . . ah . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4470.463","u": "Ja . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4471.002","u": ". . . they told us that the Germans had . . . ah . . . had . . . ah . . . blown up half of the city. And he even told me the different quarters which had been blown up. He talk&#226; . . . he talked about the Republique . . . the Quarter of the Republique, the Quarter of the Opera."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4484.723","u": "Where did they talk about it, in Auschwitz?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4486.170","u": "In Auschwitz. He told me that all these quarters in Paris had been blown up by the Germans before they left."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4490.876","u": "Aha . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4491.368","u": "So we . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4491.450","u": "So in Auschwitz they knew already that the Germans had left Paris?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4493.597","u": "Yes. It was in . . . in August or September, &#39;44."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4496.744","u": "And that they were talking freely; so you knew what was going on."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4499.499","u": "Well, we knew. You see, we . . . we knew what was going on. Some of the girls were working with high officers who had broadcastings in their rooms so sometime they manage to hear."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4507.121","u": "[simultaneously] Eh . . . to . . . radio sets in there?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4509.106","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4509.852","u": "Ja . . . some of them managed to hear it."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4511.162","u": "Managed to hear. Yes. They were never supposed to listen because it was . . . ah . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4515.015","u": "Ja . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4515.639","u": ". . . prohibited."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4515.913","u": "High treason?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4517.142","u": "Yes. Everything was verboten."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4520.162","u": "Tell me, in general . . . did the women fare who had to work with the Nazis? How did they behave . . . behave towards women?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4529.457","u": "Well, they didn&#39;t behave very well, I&#39;m sorry to say. That&#39;s to say, they made an exception for us who were working with them. They behaved fairly well. Of course, if they had an occasion they got drunk even if we were there or not. That was a different kind of thing; but on a general scale they treated us . . . ah . . . like machines, like automatons, you see."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4551.864","u": "Ja . . ."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4552.189","u": "&#34;Do this and do that,&#34; and . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4553.144","u": "What did they call you?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4555.403","u": "They called us with our names."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4555.672","u": "Did they call you &#34;Clara&#34; [?] ?"},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4556.738","u": "No, they called me &#34;Bondy.&#34;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4558.880","u": "Bondy. By the . . . by the last name."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4561.895","u": "Yes. Some of the girls they called by their first names."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4564.137","u": "Aha . . . well, Mrs. Bondy, it was awfully good of you."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4569.934","u": "Well, I . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4570.183","u": "I think it was worthwhile to trouble here with electricity. I will have a bill for a broken lamp."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4576.858","u": "Oh, I&#39;m sorry!"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4577.273","u": "But that was . . . [laughing] well, that&#39;s all right. We will charge it to research; and it was awfully good of you. I&#39;m glad I have met you."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4584.183","u": "Oh, that&#39;s OK."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4585.249","u": "Thank you very much. See that you get me somebody else."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4588.204","u": "That&#39;s all right [unintelligible]. Somebody else? From Auschwitz I haven&#39;t got [unintelligible, away from microphone] . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4591.021","u": "Well, Auschwitz or some other place."},    {"who": "Nelly Bondy", "start": "4593.366","u": "All right [?] [far from microphone]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4595.143","u": "Eh, this concludes . . . Spool . . . 61 . . . taken at the . . . headquarters of the Joint Distribution Committee on August 22nd, 1946, in Paris. A Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording."}        ]
